Let R be the ring of 2x2 matrices over the complex numbers C. Consider the two subrings S and T given by:

S = { A ∈ R : A is upper triangular matrix }
T = { A ∈ R : A is diagonal matrix }

Calculate the product of the orders of S and T as subgroups of the multiplicative group of invertible matrices GL(2,C).
